$ SQL Server: sp_helptext
@ sp_helptext

`sp_helptext` shows the definitions of some → development/databases/SQL-Server/objects[objects]:
  • user defined rules
  • (unencrypted) stored procedures, functions, triggers
  • → development/databases/SQL-Server/sql/create/table/columns/computed/division-by-zero[computed columns]
  • `check` constraints
  • views
  • system stored procedures

sa:

  → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys/objects/stored-procedures/sp_help[`sp_help`]

  → development/databases/SQL-Server/objects#mssql-show-obj-definition[Showing object definitions]
